						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p>This is too fragmentary a piece. However, it records a gift of a lamp (detail lost) to the temple of the god. Tiruvālakkōyiluḍaiya-nāynār of the place (name lost, but evidently the same Tirukkachchūr occuring in No. 306. etc., above), by a certain Porudapiḷḷai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Abhimānabhūshaṇamāṇikkam, daughter of Ariyapillai, a <hi rend="italic">dēvaraḍiyāḷ</hi> of the same temple. It seems that the gift was accepted by Āḻvāṉ •••••] <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kaṇṇāyira-bhaṭṭan of Bhāradvāja [gōtra], who had right of worship in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
